<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 1216/1999 of 10 June 1999 amending Regulation No 17: first Regulation implementing Articles 81 and 82 of the Treaty(1) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1216/1999, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust nr. 17: esimest m&auml;&auml;rust EM&Uuml; asutamislepingu artiklite 81 ja 82 rakendamise kohta (1) 10. juuni 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 83 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eelk&otilde;ige selle artiklit 83, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament(3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee(4), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (4) </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas Article 4(2) of Regulation No 17(5) dispenses a number of agreements, decisions and concerted practices from the requirement of notification prior to exemption under Article 4(1); </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1) m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 17 (5) artikli 4 l&otilde;ikega 2 vabastatakse hulk kokkuleppeid, otsuseid ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevusi teatamisn&otilde;udest enne, kui tehakse artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud erand; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas this dispensation relates in particular to agreements, decisions and concerted practices where the only parties thereto are undertakings from one Member State and the agreements, decisions or practices do not relate either to imports or exports between Member States, or where not more than two undertakings are party thereto and the agreements only restrict the freedom of one party to the contract in determining the prices or conditions of business on which the goods he has obtained from the other party to the contract may be resold; whereas this dispensation does not cover mot agreements caught by Articles 81(1) of the Treaty which are entered into by two or more undertakings, each operating, for the purposes of the agreement, at a different level of the production or distribution chain, and which relate to the conditions under which the parties may purchase, sell or resell certain goods or services ("vertical agreements"); </inglise>
<eesti> 2) see vabastus h&otilde;lmab eelk&otilde;ige kokkuleppeid, otsuseid ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevusi, mille ainsad osapooled on &uuml;he liikmesriigi ettev&otilde;tjad ning kokkulepped, otsused ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevus ei k&auml;sitle liikmesriikidevahelist importi ega eksporti, v&otilde;i kui nende osapooled ei ole rohkem kui kaks ettev&otilde;tjat ja kokkulepped piiravad ainult &uuml;he lepinguosalise vabadust m&auml;&auml;rata teiselt lepinguosaliselt saadud kaupade edasim&uuml;&uuml;gi hindu v&otilde;i &auml;ritegevuse tingimusi; see vabastus ei h&otilde;lma enamikku asutamislepingu artikli 81 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kokkulepetest, mille s&otilde;lmivad kaks v&otilde;i enam ettev&otilde;tjat, kellest iga&uuml;ks tegutseb kokkuleppe eesm&auml;rgil tootmis- v&otilde;i turustusahela eri tasandil, ja mis k&auml;sitlevad tingimusi, mida t&auml;ites osapooled v&otilde;ivad teatavaid kaupu v&otilde;i teenuseid osta, m&uuml;&uuml;a v&otilde;i edasi m&uuml;&uuml;a ("vertikaalkokkulepped"); </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas on 22 January 1997 the Commission published a Green Paper on Vertical Restraints in EC Competition Policy which generated a wide-ranging public debate on the application of Article 81(1) and (3) of the Treaty to vertical agreements; whereas the response from Member States, the European Parliament, the Economic and Social Committee, the Committee of the Regions and interested parties has been generally in favour of reform of Community competition policy in this area; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) komisjon avaldas 22. jaanuaril 1997 rohelise raamatu vertikaalpiirangutest E&Uuml; konkurentsipoliitikas, mis tekitas laiaulatusliku avaliku m&otilde;ttevahetuse asutamislepingu artikli 81 l&otilde;igete 1 ja 3 kohaldamise kohta vertikaalkokkulepete suhtes; liikmesriikide, Euroopa Parlamendi, majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee, regioonide komitee ning huvitatud osapoolte vastuses on &uuml;ldiselt pooldatud &uuml;henduse konkurentsipoliitika reformi selles valdkonnas; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas any such reform must meet the two requirements of ensuring effective protection of competition and providing adequate legal certainty for firms; whereas, in order to achieve these objectives, the Commission has been empowered by the Council to declare, by regulation and in accordance with Article 81(3) of the Treaty, that Article 81(1) is not applicable to categories of vertical agreements; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) iga selline reform peab vastama kahele n&otilde;udele, nimelt tagama konkurentsi t&otilde;husa kaitse ja andma ettev&otilde;tjatele piisava &otilde;iguskindluse; nende eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks on n&otilde;ukogu volitanud komisjoni kuulutama m&auml;&auml;rusega ja vastavalt asutamislepingu artikli 81 l&otilde;ikele 3, et artikli 81 l&otilde;iget 1 ei kohaldata vertikaalkokkulepete liikide suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas reform of the regulatory framework applicable to vertical agreements must in addition take account of the need to simplify administrative supervision which would result in a reduction of the number of notifications of vertical agreements; whereas thee should be a reduction of the incentive to notify vertical agreements which are in compliance with the policy of the Commission and the case-law of the Court of Justice and the Court of first instance; whereas, to achieve that objective, the Commission should be empowered to grant individual exemption for vertical agreements caught by Article 81(1) of the Treaty from the date on which they were entered into; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) vertikaalkokkulepete suhtes kohaldatava reguleeriva raamistiku reform peab lisaks v&otilde;tma arvesse vajadust lihtsustada haldusj&auml;relevalvet, mille tulemusel v&auml;heneks vertikaalkokkulepetest teatamiste hulk; tuleks v&auml;hendada komisjoni poliitikat ja Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Kohtu ning esimese astme kohtu pretsedendi&otilde;igust j&auml;rgivatest vertikaalkokkulepetest teatamise soodustust; selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks peaks komisjonil olema &otilde;igus teha &uuml;ksikerandeid asutamislepingu artikli 81 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud vertikaalkokkulepete kohta alates nende s&otilde;lmimise kuup&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas the requirement of notification prior to exemption imposes on firms which are party to vertical agreements an unnecessary administrative burden; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) enne erandi tegemist paneb teatamisn&otilde;ue vertikaalkokkuleppe osapooltest ettev&otilde;tjatele tarbetu halduskoorma; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas the agreements referred to in Article 4(2) of Regulation No 17 are dispensed from the requirement of notification prior to exemption; whereas the purpose of this dispensation is to reduce the number of notifications, which enables the Commission to concentrate its efforts on supervising those restrictive agreements which are the most damaging to competition; whereas, therefore, this amendment does not entail any relaxation in the supervision which the Commission has a duty to exercise under Article 81(1); </inglise>
<eesti> 7) m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 17 artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud kokkulepped on enne erandi tegemist teatamisest vabastatud; selle vabastuse eesm&auml;rk on teatamiste hulga v&auml;hendamine, mis v&otilde;imaldab komisjonil koondada oma j&otilde;upingutused nende piiravate kokkulepete j&auml;relevalvele, mis on konkurentsile k&otilde;ige kahjulikumad; seet&otilde;ttu ei h&otilde;lma k&auml;esolev muudatus j&auml;relevalve l&otilde;dvendamist, mille tegemine on vastavalt artikli 81 l&otilde;ikele 1 komisjoni kohustus; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas the scope of Article 4(2) of Regulation No 17 should therefore be extended, and all vertical agreements should be dispensed from the requirement of notification prior to exemption, </inglise>
<eesti> 8) m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 17 artikli 4 l&otilde;ike 2 reguleerimisala tuleks seet&otilde;ttu laiendada ja vabastada k&otilde;ik vertikaalkokkulepped enne erandi tegemist teatamisn&otilde;udest, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Point 2 of Article 4(2) of Regulation No 17 shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse nr 17 artikli 4 l&otilde;ike 2 punkt 2 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "2. (a) the agreements or concerted practices are entered into by two or more undertakings, each operating, for the purposes of the agreement, at a different level of the production or distribution chain, and relate to the conditions under which the parties may purchase, sell or resell certain goods or services; </inglise>
<eesti> "2. a) kokkulepped v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevused s&otilde;lmivad kaks v&otilde;i mitu ettev&otilde;tjat, kellest iga&uuml;ks tegutseb kokkuleppe kohaldamisel tootmis- v&otilde;i turustusahela eri tasandil, ja k&auml;sitlevad tingimusi, mille alusel osapooled v&otilde;ivad teatud kaupu v&otilde;i teenuseid osta, m&uuml;&uuml;a v&otilde;i edasi m&uuml;&uuml;a; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) not more than two undertakings are party thereto, and the agreements only impose restrictions on the exercise of the rights of the assignee or user of industrial property rights, in particular patents, utility models, designs or trade marks, or of the person entitled under a contract to the assignment, or grant, of the right to use a method of manufacture or knowledge relating to the use and to the application of industrial processes". </inglise>
<eesti> b) mille osapooled on ainult kaks ettev&otilde;tjat, ja kokkulepped kehtestavad ainult kitsendusi t&ouml;&ouml;stusomandi &otilde;iguste valdaja v&otilde;i kasutaja &otilde;iguste teostamisele - eriti patentide, kasulike mudelite, t&ouml;&ouml;stusdisainilahenduste ja kaubam&auml;rkide puhul - v&otilde;i isiku &otilde;igusi, kes on lepingu alusel saanud &otilde;iguse kasutada valmistamismeetodit v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;stusprotsessidega seotud oskusteavet". </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
